dialogue.introduction: I'm Suzuya! What a lively fleet it is. I'll be in your care!
dialogue.library_intro: Suzuya's number 3 of the Mogami-class heavy cruisers. I was born at the Yokosuka Naval Arsenal~ hehheh. See, cruiser names come from rivers, so 'Suzuya' comes from the Suzuya river in Sakhalin. Did ya know?
dialogue.secretary1: Oh! If it isn't the Admiral! 'Sup!
dialogue.secretary2: Oh, what'cha doing?... What'cha wanna do?
dialogue.secretary3: I told you not to touch Suzuya's deck knee socks like that! Geez!
dialogue.secretaryidle: Admiraaall, I'm seriously bored, aren't we gonna sortie? Sor-tie-!!
dialogue.secretarymarried: That Kumano, I hope she's doing okay... Right, Admiral?
dialogue.wedding: "A~dmira~l! It's a bit of a serious talk, but thanks for taking a ship like Suzuya this far! Again, 'grats...eh..ah...umm...anyway, as always, please take care of me!"
dialogue.show_players_score: Here~, a report addressed to Admiral~
dialogue.joining_a_fleet: Mogami-class heavy cruiser, Suzuya! Here I go!
dialogue.equipment1: Ooh, I won't lose to Kumano like this~
dialogue.docking_minor_damage: Man, you really do get hungry after exercise, don't you?
dialogue.ship_construction: Looks like a cute girl has come, y'know?
dialogue.return_from_sortie: The fleet has returned~, good work~!
dialogue.mvp: Well, isn't the result obvious? Suzuya's the type that gets better if you praise her. Praise more, okay!
dialogue.moderately_damaged: Noo.. This is embarrasing... Don't look! Aaah~ my spirit's dropping...
dialogue.sunk: C-crap... my torpedo tube, exploded...? That... could be bad...
dialogue.white_day_2015: Woah! What's this package? You gonna give it to me? Ah hah, thank you, Admiral! What did I get, what did I get? Heehee...
dialogue.early_summer_2015: Argh... I think it's getting a little hotter... Uhh, it's kinda getting steamy... Is Kumano fine?
dialogue.midsummer_2015: Summer! It's Summer! Kumano, let's go for a swim in our new swimsuits! Huh? Ehh... Admiral, do you want to come too?
dialogue.fall_2015: Autumn, huh? This season kinda makes feel a lil' bit down. Right, Kumano? Uhm, Kumano? You listening?
dialogue.christmas_2015: Merry Christmas, Merry Christmas! Admiral, Merry Christmas to you~! Alright, give me my present~! Uuunn~
dialogue.new_year_2016: Admiral, Happy New Year to ya, take care of me this year, too! Suzuya's glad to bring in the new year as well. Now! Where's my New Year's gift~
dialogue.setsubun_2016: Setsubun, eh... Kumano, do we have any plans for Setsubun? Ahh... Looks like she's eating something. Ohh...
dialogue.valentines_day_2016: Oi..., Admiral, here's suzuya's chocolate, O~pen~wide! Fufu', dont forget I expect something in retun, Nihhihihi

hourly.0000: Midnight 12 o'clock. This is when the night really starts, ya know?
hourly.0100: 1 o'clock, huh... You're also a night-owl, Admiral?
hourly.0300: 3 o'clock already! It's come to this, let's go all night!
hourly.0500: 5 o'clock huh? Man, I wanna take a nap...
hourly.0600: It's 6 o'clock, let's sleep from now!
hourly.0700: 7 o'clock! A~ah, time to do the morning news~
hourly.0800: Ta dah! Stay tuned from 8 o'clock!
hourly.0900: It's 9 o'clock! Let's go strong today as well!
hourly.1000: Yeah, 10 o'clock! Where we goin' today?
hourly.1200: Yea~h, it's 12 o'clock! I wanna eat curry today too~
hourly.1300: Already 1 o'clock? It's not Friday, but it's Curry Time! Curry just for the ship girls!
hourly.1400: 2 o'clock! Admiral, afternoon nap, ya know, nap!
hourly.1600: 4 o'clock. Hey, why don't we get some tea?
hourly.1800: 6 o'clock! I'm a bit nervous, somehow~
hourly.1900: It's 7 o'clock. I wonder what's for dinner~
hourly.2000: 8 o'clock huh, from here on in it's my time!
hourly.2100: Well, it's 9 o'clock. Are the expeditions over?
hourly.2200: Already 10 o'clock, huh? Man, the day goes fast...
hourly.2300: 11 o'clock! Oh yeah! My night engine is all fired up!
